---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="CV" description="Curriculum vitae of Sudarshan Koirala, Senior GenAI Engineer, former Data Scientist at KONE, and AI educator.">
  <div class="container document-container cv-container">
    <header class="document-header">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Curriculum Vitae</p>
        <h1>Sudarshan Koirala</h1>
        <p>Senior GenAI Engineer at KONE · AI, data science, MLOps, and technical education</p>
      </div>
      <button class="print-link" type="button" onclick="window.print()">
        <span class="button-icon icon-print" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span>Print / Save PDF</span>
      </button>
    </header>

    <section class="document-section">
      <h2>Profile</h2>
      <p>
        Sudarshan Koirala is a Senior GenAI Engineer at KONE in Espoo, Finland, with a background in
        data science, machine learning, software engineering, and physics. His work focuses on practical
        enterprise AI systems, generative AI, MLOps, data platforms, and education through Data Science Basics.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="document-section">
      <h2>Professional Appointments</h2>
      <div class="document-item">
        <div class="document-item-head">
          <h3>Senior GenAI Engineer · KONE Oyj</h3>
          <span>Current role · Espoo, Finland</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Leads and contributes to AI/ML-driven generative AI solutions, automated ML workflows,
          SRE practices for AI systems, LLM prototyping, and MLOps guidance for data science teams.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="document-item">
        <div class="document-item-head">
          <h3>Data Scientist · KONE Oyj</h3>
          <span>Earlier KONE role · Espoo, Finland</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Built data science and machine learning solutions using Python, SQL, cloud tooling, and ML workflows
          before progressing into the Senior GenAI Engineer role.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="document-item">
        <div class="document-item-head">
          <h3>Thesis Worker -> Machine Learning Trainee · Nokia Solutions and Networks Oyj</h3>
          <span>2020 - 2021</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Worked on NLP event discovery from social media feeds with spaCy and pre-trained models,
          implemented deep neural networks for tabular data, and served as scrum master for a 15-person trainee team.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="document-item">
        <div class="document-item-head">
          <h3>Content Creator · Data Science Basics</h3>
          <span>2022 - Present</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Creates public tutorials and articles on AI, data science, Databricks, LLMs, developer tools,
          agent workflows, and applied machine learning.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="document-section">
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <div class="document-item compact">
        <h3>Aalto University</h3>
        <p>M.Sc. (Technology), Computer Science · 2019 - 2021 · GPA 4.27/5</p>
        <p>Major: Big Data and Large-Scale Computing · Minor: Machine Learning, Data Science and Artificial Intelligence</p>
      </div>
      <div class="document-item compact">
        <h3>Metropolia University of Applied Sciences</h3>
        <p>B.Eng., Software Engineering · 2018</p>
      </div>
      <div class="document-item compact">
        <h3>Tribhuvan University, Nepal</h3>
        <p>B.Sc., Physics · 2010</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="document-section">
      <h2>Technical Areas</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Generative AI, RAG, LLM prototyping, applied AI engineering, and enterprise AI workflows.</li>
        <li>MLOps, model tracking, automated ML workflows, CI/CD, reliability, and production readiness.</li>
        <li>Databricks, Apache Spark, PySpark, SQL, Python, AWS, Azure, Azure OpenAI, Amazon Bedrock, and MLflow.</li>
        <li>Technical education, tutorial design, and developer-focused AI communication.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="document-section">
      <h2>Selected Public Work</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Data Science Basics YouTube channel covering AI, data science, Databricks, LLMs, and developer tools.</li>
        <li><a href="https://medium.com/@sudarshan-koirala/omnigent-the-meta-harness-for-all-your-ai-agents-4c91d2d8dfae" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Omnigent: The Meta-Harness for All Your AI Agents</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://medium.com/@sudarshan-koirala/prompt-vs-context-vs-harness-engineering-the-three-layers-around-every-ai-model-b31628b55845" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Prompt vs Context vs Harness Engineering</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://medium.com/@sudarshan-koirala/databricks-data-ai-summit-2026-every-big-announcement-explained-simply-e5b613c3abc1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Databricks Data + AI Summit 2026: Every Big Announcement, Explained Simply</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="document-section">
      <h2>Selected Tutorials</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>30 Days of Databricks tutorials for practical lakehouse and AI workflows.</li>
        <li>LangChain and LlamaIndex walkthroughs for RAG and agent-style applications.</li>
        <li>AI developer tool reviews and implementation notes for modern coding workflows.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="document-section">
      <h2>Professional Interests</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Reliable enterprise AI systems and MLOps practices for production teams.</li>
        <li>LLM application design, evaluation, observability, and workflow automation.</li>
        <li>Teaching complex AI and data platform concepts in practical, beginner-friendly ways.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="document-section">
      <h2>Languages</h2>
      <p>English (fluent) · Nepalese (native) · Finnish (beginner) · Hindi (satisfactory)</p>
    </section>

    <section class="document-section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:basicsdatascience@gmail.com">basicsdatascience@gmail.com</a> ·
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sudarshan-koirala/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a> ·
        <a href="https://github.com/sudarshan-koirala" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a> ·
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@datasciencebasics" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
